[SN]TITLE[SN]
Weston beach walker rescued after getting stuck in mud

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been rescued by Somerset coastguards after getting stuck in mud on Weston-super-Mare beach.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
A boat and a helicopter were involved in the operation which took place near the Grand Pier at about 14:00 BST on Friday.
Specialist equipment was used to free the man who was cold and wet but uninjured.
Coastguard officer Ian Thomas advised the public to take great care around estuarial mud and "not to take risks".
